American singer-songwriter and actress Beyonce has become the most awarded artiste in the Grammy’s history. Beyonce took home four awards on Sunday night, the 5th of February, to become the most-awarded artiste with a total of 32 trophies. She won Grammy awards for best R&B song, best dance/electronic album, best dance/electronic recording, and best traditional R&B performance. She won 32 Grammys, making her the most-awarded artist of all time. Speaking during the award night, Beyonce said “I’m trying not to be too emotional and just receive this night. Thank you to the queer community for your love and inventing the genre. God bless you.”